title: 820-00165 Vcore Present, CPU Warm, No Chime
message: Hello all! Got an 820-00165 board here that has all power rails, CPU gets warm, but no chime. Suspecting maybe BIOS IS BAD, however every link I found here on the forum are broken. Could anyone pls send me a known working file?

title: 820-00165 Vcore Present, CPU Warm, No Chime
message:
I posted some BIOS links for 00165 a week ago.
Did you check them?
[URL unfurl="true"]https://boards.rossmanngroup.com/threads/820-00165-not-booting-after-big-sur-upgrade.61298/[/URL]

title: 820-00165 Vcore Present, CPU Warm, No Chime
message: Thanks for replying! Tried both and I have same result. Fan spins at max, no chime, VCORE stable at 1,8V. Any ideas? I suspect bad PCH.

title: 820-00165 Vcore Present, CPU Warm, No Chime
message:
PLT_RESET_L goes high?
Any history fault available?

Check all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and traces.
Also check series resistors from LPC bus.
